  <description><![CDATA[<p>This high quality stylish hotel has really established itself as one of <a data-udi="umb://document/7bd0ea2aff2942389cbf8acdba0a0e77" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7bd0ea2aff2942389cbf8acdba0a0e77}" title="Soldeu">Soldeu's</a> absolute favourites with Inghams guests. This impressive complex boasts bright and airy bedrooms with fantastic views, an extensive buffet restaurant including display cooking, great children's facilities with a lovely indoor play area, and an excellent modern spa area and pool offering a place to relax after a day of skiing.</p>
<h2>Fantastic and friendly</h2>
<p>The rooms have been recently renovated as has the wonderful lounge and lobby areas and spa, and the hotel has obtained an official 5 star accreditation. The atmosphere is informal and friendly especially in the comfortable lobby lounge which has big picture windows looking at the mountains and the slopes. The service here is attentive and a warm welcome is assured.</p>
<h2>Sustainable wellness</h2>
<p>The Park Piolets Mountain Resort &amp; Spa wellness facilities promote sustainability through their treatments that are performed with probiotic and natural products that are free from preservatives and are respectful to the environment. The spa is specifically designed with nature in mind, prioritising the flow of natural light and natural fibre fabrics. You'll find a large water area, treatments cabins and a gym where you can really relax and become one with nature.</p>
<h2>Lounge bar</h2>
<p>The lounge and bar invite you to end the evening over a drink with friends and family. With direct access to the hotels <span>Moët &amp; Chandon Terrace where you can enjoy Andorras sunny days, the space was designed by Pilar Líbano, the prestigious decorator, and creates an cosy and unique atmosphere with a fireplace and comfortable sofas - perfect for sipping cocktails.</span></p>
<h3>Why is this an Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Spa and wellness facilities</strong> - After a day of skiing, there is nowhere better to relax than the spa area with an indoor pool, sauna and Turkish bath. There's also a fitness room and well-being treatments available.</p>
<p><strong>Gastronomy</strong> - Try varied cuisines at the dinner buffet where there are eight different cooking show zones each day. There is also a lovely bar and terrace, perfect for enjoying a cocktail after dinner.</p>
<p><strong>Luxury hotel</strong> -  The stylish and modern Park Piolets ticks all the boxes for a winter holiday with spacious bedrooms, tasty food and a wellness area. Plus getting on the slopes couldn't be easier with a free shuttle service running each day.</p>]]></description>
